                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">ideas of aa's most of them are just final versions of aa's that are atm worthless (aa's that are behind stat/resist in usefulness and are only gotten to say "hey i've got em all")
<br />

<br />
A) requiers all breathing aa's maxed. perma EB effect (your lungs have become so adapt in water they can now pull O2 from the water)
<br />

<br />
B)requiers all fizzle remover aa's.*there are a lot of them remember* and maybe SCM3. maybe a few lvls but will eventually include every spell in the game (effectivly removing the chance to fizzle from your charactor)
<br />

<br />
C)perma spell haste. there are a lot of ways to implement this.
<br />
--one way is to create 5 lvls for about 5aa's each. each lvl all spells go down in cast time by .1 seconds, finally ending at .5 seconds removed from all spells, no spell can be hasted below 2seconds with this, and maybe charm and CH are excluded. (mez is now 2second woot)
<br />
--a second way to implement this that a lot of people wont like (including m heh but heck) could even be two forms of it. decreases cast time of spells in your specization (the one above 200) the second form increases cast rate in your secondary specization (requires having one of course) each form has 5 lvls and goes up to .5 seconds reduction etc.
<br />
---of course both would stack with everything but can't make it faster then 2seconds.
<br />

<br />
the spell haste is a dream idea, but considering their cost the first two are very pratical, i mean wouldn't 25+aa's be worth a perma EB? maybe require lvl 70 (or whatever the lvl cap will be) for them as well.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=319303" target="_blank" class="postlink">Olmec</a> <span style="font-style: italic">Let Them Come</span>
<br />
The Band of The Broken Bow
<br />
Tribunal Server</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
