                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">For AA I'd choose to give all pure caster, wis and int an additional spell gem.  Half of the AA they come up with serves that purpose anyways, why not just make it a generic one, I'm surprised they haven't already done this by now.  This AA would sell for a mint as well.  
<br />

<br />
Second, I'd choose to lower the recast times on all ench nukes.  They are up there, and this can't be done with equipment, or spells, or anything, so if it was done with an AA that'd be perfect.  
<br />

<br />
Third, I don't like the idea of adding an AA to fix an old AA, I would prefer they just fix the freakin original.  So if they add an AA to make doppleganger useful, I will probably just feel insulted, if the first rank of the AA is like 5 aa then why not just charge me 35 aa to get the first rank of doppleganger and have it do that effect.  There's no reason to give me 30 aa worth of something that I can't use.  
<br />

<br />
Fourth, I think innate Invis is not asking too much, tons of other classes have it, and it's pretty nice to have, esp when we are pacifying.  Which brings me to the fifth, how about an increased chance to pacify, or not agro when pacify gets resisted.  Make it so that enchanters are better at it then bards and clerics.  Although that probably won't happen, since bards are dependant on pacify to fulfill their niche as puller in an adventure.  But they already have an escape ability that makes them flawless pullers anyways.  
<br />

<br />
Sixth, Ultimate Specialization, you now have a very rare chance of using NO MANA! when you make a second specialization check.  Make it be like only when you make the first one, that way it would've reduced mana anyways, and now you can make a second check to see if it's totally mana free.  Or make both checks, only the mana free one doesn't work unless both are succesfull.  
<br />

<br />
Seventh, A combination memory blur and pacify, this would be infinitely useful, this could be either a spell or an AA ability.  This is what doppleganger should've been.  Naturally it should work on lower lvl mobs then your typical pacify does, otherwise there'd be no reason to use the old pacify.  Perhaps make it work only on mobs a few lvls lower then the spell lvl, whereas pacify tends to work on higher lvl mobs.
<br />

<br />
Eighth, make an AA that gives us some kind of benefit from using illusions, or maybe just gives each illusion a new special benefit, that makes them more interesting.  The thing that would make illusions interesting buffs is that you can only have one on at a time.  So even if they were each uber powerful buffs, you'd have to choose the one you wanted for the situation.  Would make for some very interesting looking groups anyways.  
<br />

<br />
It disturbs me that I can come up with about 5 totally original ideas and 3 obvious ones in a couple of hours based on experience in gameplay and SOE can't create more then a couple for us in an entire expansion.  Other then the fixes for spells and such that shouldn't even probably need to be fixed.  I.E. mem blur.  Here's hoping that they can come up with something that actually piques my interest in OOW.  Building AA out of habit now more then out of excitement for the newest upgrades.
<br />

<br />
-Saxony</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
